Tested byTestaro, procedure ts24
Scored byTestilo, procedure tsp24
Digested byTestilo, procedure tdp24

Introduction

This is a digest of results from a battery of accessibility Tests.

The battery includes 1353 automated accessibility tests drawn from ten different packages: Alfa, Axe, Continuum, Equal Access, HTML CodeSniffer, Nu Html Checker, QualWeb, Tenon, Testaro, and WAVE.

These tests were run on the web page named above and gave the page a score of 1945, where 0 would be perfect.

Issue summary

Special issues

log: Score 287. This is based on the amount of browser error logging and miscellaneous logging during the tests.

preventions: Score 100. This is based on tests that the page did not allow to be run. That impedes accessibility progress and risks interfering with tools that users with disabilities need.

solos: Score 46. This is based on issues reported by unclassified tests. Details are in the report.

Classified issues

Issue textContrastAA

WCAG: 1.4.3

Score: 240

Issue reports in this category:

  • Package alfa, test r69, score 163 (Text outside widget has subminimum contrast)
  • Package axe, test color-contrast, score 55 (Element has insufficient color contrast)
  • Package htmlcs, test e:AAA.1_4_6.G18.Fail, score 20 (Contrast between the text and its background is less than 4.5:1)
  • Package qualWeb, test QW-ACT-R37, score 4 (Text has less than the minimum contrast)
  • Package wave, test c:contrast, score 108 (Very low contrast)

Issue roleBad

WCAG: 4.1.2

Score: 160

Issue reports in this category:

  • Package testaro, test role, score 158 (Nonexistent or implicit-overriding role)

Issue contentBeyondLandmarks

WCAG: 1.3.6

Score: 132

Issue reports in this category:

  • Package alfa, test r57, score 104 (Perceivable text content is not included in any landmark)
  • Package axe, test region, score 8 (Some page content is not contained by landmarks)
  • Package ibm, test Rpt_Aria_OrphanedContent_Native_Host_Sematics, score 58 (Content does not reside within an element with a landmark role)

Issue focusableHidden

WCAG: 4.1.2

Score: 118

Issue reports in this category:

  • Package alfa, test r17, score 12 (Tab-focusable element is or has an ancestor that is aria-hidden)
  • Package axe, test aria-hidden-focus, score 9 (ARIA hidden element is focusable or contains a focusable element)
  • Package ibm, test aria_hidden_focus_misuse, score 108 (Focusable element is within the subtree of an element with aria-hidden set to true)

Issue imageNoText

WCAG: 1.1.1

Score: 96

Issue reports in this category:

  • Package alfa, test r2, score 36 (Image has no accessible name)
  • Package axe, test image-alt, score 36 (Image has no text alternative)
  • Package continuum, test 89, score 36 (img element has no mechanism that allows an accessible name to be calculated)
  • Package htmlcs, test e:AAA.1_1_1.H37, score 12 (img element has no alt attribute)
  • Package ibm, test WCAG20_Img_HasAlt, score 40 (Image has no alt attribute conveying its meaning, or alt="" if decorative)
  • Package wave, test e:alt_missing, score 16 (Text alternative is missing)

Issue linkForcesNewWindow

WCAG: 3.2.5

Score: 74

Issue reports in this category:

  • Package tenon, test 218, score 72 (Link opens in a new window without user control)

Issue contrastAAA

Score: 73

Issue reports in this category:

  • Package alfa, test r66, score 51 (Text contrast less than AAA requires)

  • Package htmlcs, test e:AAA.1_4_6.G17.Fail, score 27 (Text has insufficient contrast)
  • Package qualWeb, test QW-ACT-R76, score 1 (Text has less than the enhanced minimum contrast)
